(Foei could tell)

277
00:16:10,253 --> 00:16:11,913
(I was struggling with money.)

278
00:16:12,531 --> 00:16:14,138
(Then Foei recommended this job to me.)

279
00:16:14,632 --> 00:16:16,575
(Pick whichever you like.)

280
00:16:18,288 --> 00:16:20,142
Hello.

281
00:16:20,972 --> 00:16:24,645
I'll take the one in the middle,
in the white tank top.

282
00:16:29,914 --> 00:16:33,280
The crab's climbing.

283
00:16:34,042 --> 00:16:35,922
Hey!

284
00:16:36,058 --> 00:16:37,394
Why?

285
00:16:37,394 --> 00:16:39,795
Going down now. Wow, going down now.

286
00:16:39,795 --> 00:16:41,743
Don't block.

287
00:16:42,427 --> 00:16:45,235
Sorry!

288
00:16:45,235 --> 00:16:46,824
I'll punch you!

289
00:16:46,859 --> 00:16:48,325
(It wasn't easy at first.)

290
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:51,327
(Actually, it was incredibly hard.)

291
00:16:51,706 --> 00:16:54,304
The crab's climbing.

292
00:16:55,406 --> 00:16:57,207
So, what do you do for a living?

293
00:16:57,525 --> 00:16:59,839
What kind of host
asks a question like that?

294
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:04,183
I came here to find happiness,

295
00:17:04,183 --> 00:17:07,255
but you're ruining my life like this?

296
00:17:11,264 --> 00:17:13,082
Darn it, Wayu!

297
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:14,389
You again?

298
00:17:14,389 --> 00:17:16,048
You never listen to a word I say!

299
00:17:16,084 --> 00:17:18,062
You're ruining everything!
All my customers are running away!

300
00:17:18,296 --> 00:17:20,150
Tai! Get over here!

301
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:21,541
Coming!

302
00:17:21,612 --> 00:17:23,925
Look at your friend! No matter
how much I teach him, he never learns!

303
00:17:23,925 --> 00:17:24,737
My business is going down the drain!

304
00:17:24,737 --> 00:17:25,602
Get over here!

305
00:17:25,638 --> 00:17:27,492
- Calm down.
- Deal with him right now.

306
00:17:27,492 --> 00:17:28,499
I'll handle him.

307
00:17:28,499 --> 00:17:29,381
I'll handle him.

308
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:31,606
- But for now, please just step back.
- Wait!

309
00:17:31,606 --> 00:17:32,348
Wait!

310
00:17:32,348 --> 00:17:34,079
Let me get him first!

311
00:17:35,845 --> 00:17:36,904
Take that!

312
00:17:37,946 --> 00:17:39,147
Watch out!

313
00:17:43,508 --> 00:17:45,168
(But I'm very lucky)

314
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,560
(to have a friend)

315
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:49,954
(who constantly teaches and guides me.)

316
00:17:54,209 --> 00:17:56,682
(In my first few nights,
I only got two drinks per night.)

317
00:17:57,812 --> 00:18:00,072
(From then on, my drink sales
started climbing.)

318
00:18:02,314 --> 00:18:03,444
(With my first month's salary,)

319
00:18:04,028 --> 00:18:06,500
(I earned enough to pay off
a good portion of my mom's debt.)

320
00:18:11,144 --> 00:18:12,663
So that's pretty much my life.

321
00:18:13,493 --> 00:18:15,135
There's probably no other job

322
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:16,954
that pays as well as this one.

323
00:18:20,802 --> 00:18:21,632
Here.

324
00:18:22,022 --> 00:18:22,958
Let's have a drink.

325
00:18:25,289 --> 00:18:26,931
No thanks. I don't dare drink.

326
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:29,050
I won't have enough money to pay.

327
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:32,670
That's exactly why you should drink.

328
00:18:32,935 --> 00:18:35,849
Because today
I'm going to squeeze you dry.

329
00:18:38,992 --> 00:18:40,705
Alright then. Let's do it.

330
00:18:53,225 --> 00:18:55,891
Excuse me, Ms. Rose?
May I take a photo with you?

331
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,533
- My pleasure.
- Thank you!

332
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:58,999
One, two, three.

333
00:18:59,564 --> 00:19:01,295
I'm your big fan.

334
00:19:02,054 --> 00:19:03,837
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

335
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:11,254
Hello.

336
00:19:11,766 --> 00:19:13,461
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

337
00:19:13,461 --> 00:19:15,969
I didn't see your name in the bookings.

338
00:19:22,432 --> 00:19:24,728
I'm Rose, Krit's girlfriend.

339
00:19:30,078 --> 00:19:30,908
I'm Wayu.

340
00:19:35,270 --> 00:19:36,894
We met during a case.

341
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:41,044
Nice to meet you.

342
00:19:41,503 --> 00:19:42,386
Nice to meet you, too.

343
00:19:48,055 --> 00:19:48,973
Let me take this call.

344
00:19:59,974 --> 00:20:02,906
I'll leave you two to it.

345
00:20:03,329 --> 00:20:04,901
Enjoy your meal.

346
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:06,755
Thank you.

347
00:20:06,755 --> 00:20:08,291
It was a pleasure meeting you.

348
00:20:08,486 --> 00:20:09,598
Me too.

349
00:20:20,405 --> 00:20:22,471
This place is as "expensive"
as its owner, huh?

350
00:20:27,610 --> 00:20:29,182
(Sorry, but I need to hurry off.)

351
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,912
It's okay. I understand.

352
00:20:34,426 --> 00:20:36,086
Don't worry about it. I'll get the bill.

353
00:20:36,316 --> 00:20:37,640
No, I'll pay.

354
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,894
Really, it's fine.

355
00:20:38,947 --> 00:20:40,395
Excuse me. Can I scan to pay?

356
00:20:49,295 --> 00:20:50,054
Officer.

357
00:20:50,284 --> 00:20:52,438
I really intended to treat you.

358
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,316
Just you wanting to treat me

359
00:20:55,634 --> 00:20:57,065
is thanks enough.

360
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:00,296
I can afford it.

361
00:21:03,528 --> 00:21:05,681
Fine, let's go halves then.

362
00:21:06,424 --> 00:21:07,572
That way, we're even.

363
00:21:11,086 --> 00:21:12,021
Then,

364
00:21:12,868 --> 00:21:15,185
tell me your phone number.
I'll transfer the money to you.

365
00:21:15,185 --> 00:21:16,154
Let's scan then.

366
00:21:19,862 --> 00:21:20,745
Sure.

367
00:21:31,305 --> 00:21:32,294
Officer!

368
00:21:32,558 --> 00:21:33,406
Officer!

369
00:21:33,848 --> 00:21:35,790
Officer! Wait!

370
00:21:40,311 --> 00:21:42,112
The slip isn't coming through.

371
00:21:42,377 --> 00:21:44,443
Can I get your contact info?

372
00:21:44,443 --> 00:21:46,562
Just in case
I need to send the slip later.

373
00:21:47,215 --> 00:21:48,239
It's fine.

374
00:21:48,522 --> 00:21:50,235
I don't think you'd try to scam a cop.

375
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,389
I can't have that.

376
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:54,226
If I disappear,

377
00:21:54,226 --> 00:21:55,956
you won't be able to track me down.

378
00:21:56,503 --> 00:21:58,259
Please, I'd like your contact.

379
00:21:58,259 --> 00:21:59,442
I'll send the slip later.

380
00:22:00,918 --> 00:22:02,967
You can just send it via SMS.

381
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:07,293
Oh, don't be like that.

382
00:22:07,646 --> 00:22:10,048
SMS costs money.

383
00:22:16,917 --> 00:22:18,683
How about Instagram?
I'll type it in for you.

384
00:22:18,842 --> 00:22:19,707
Sure.

385
00:22:26,347 --> 00:22:28,377
I have to go deal with the case now.

386
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,461
Of course, Officer.

387
00:22:31,803 --> 00:22:32,898
Just call me "Krit."

388
00:22:35,194 --> 00:22:36,871
And when you go back to work,

389
00:22:37,313 --> 00:22:38,496
take care of yourself.

390
00:22:38,937 --> 00:22:40,103
Don't go getting your head busted again.

391
00:22:41,498 --> 00:22:42,716
Copy that, Krit!

392
00:22:43,052 --> 00:22:44,217
Next time we meet,

393
00:22:44,305 --> 00:22:47,678
it definitely won't be
as a cop and a suspect.

394
00:22:49,127 --> 00:22:49,798
Right.

395
00:22:59,139 --> 00:23:01,364
I've seen the reports on social media.

396
00:23:02,229 --> 00:23:04,013
People are ripping into the police

397
00:23:04,207 --> 00:23:05,461
over this human trafficking case.

398
00:23:07,827 --> 00:23:09,398
We need to fix our image fast

399
00:23:09,911 --> 00:23:12,224
before they start calling us useless.

400
00:23:13,478 --> 00:23:16,374
Also, that evidence you found

401
00:23:16,409 --> 00:23:18,934
regarding Chainphop's logistics business,

402
00:23:19,199 --> 00:23:21,618
I've checked it out.

403
00:23:21,618 --> 00:23:25,203
It's highly likely they're using it as a way
to move victims across to neighboring countries.

404
00:23:25,397 --> 00:23:26,174
Yes, Sir.

405
00:23:26,792 --> 00:23:28,646
I've sent a team to stake it out,

406
00:23:29,388 --> 00:23:31,454
but we still haven't found the big boss.

407
00:23:33,185 --> 00:23:34,474
I know

408
00:23:34,474 --> 00:23:37,140
it's tough and takes time,

409
00:23:37,511 --> 00:23:40,071
but I need you
to stay on top of this case.

410
00:23:41,519 --> 00:23:42,844
Got it, sir.

411
00:23:43,691 --> 00:23:44,822
I'm counting on you, Krit.

412
00:23:45,157 --> 00:23:46,729
Given the current situation,

413
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,601
we need to pick up the pace.

414
00:23:49,572 --> 00:23:50,525
Understood, Sir.

415
00:23:51,973 --> 00:23:52,892
Please.

416
00:23:53,754 --> 00:23:58,319
(Police Major General,
Investigation Inspector, Athip Phongwilai)

417
00:24:01,368 --> 00:24:03,540
Chompoo, put the soup there

418
00:24:04,741 --> 00:24:07,213
and go get some more water.

419
00:24:09,968 --> 00:24:11,592
Oh, Krit, you're back.

420
00:24:11,592 --> 00:24:12,864
Come eat with us.

421
00:24:15,654 --> 00:24:17,826
- Come on. Dad's waiting.
- Yes.

422
00:24:17,879 --> 00:24:18,673
Come on.

423
00:24:24,501 --> 00:24:25,436
Bring the water.

424
00:24:26,214 --> 00:24:29,268
Okay, it's great today.

425
00:24:29,286 --> 00:24:31,299
Father and son like all the same foods,

426
00:24:31,405 --> 00:24:32,800
so it makes cooking easy for me.

427
00:24:33,577 --> 00:24:34,460
Come on.

428
00:24:40,762 --> 00:24:41,442
Here you go.

429
00:24:42,583 --> 00:24:43,590
Thank you.

430
00:24:48,552 --> 00:24:49,717
Do your job well.

431
00:24:50,353 --> 00:24:52,913
Don't forget you have an image
to maintain.

432
00:24:53,796 --> 00:24:55,527
You only got this case

433
00:24:55,827 --> 00:24:58,882
because people respect me,
not just because of you.

434
00:25:09,353 --> 00:25:11,031
I'm feeling a bit sticky.

435
00:25:11,561 --> 00:25:12,585
I'll go shower first.

436
00:25:12,585 --> 00:25:13,521
I'll come down to eat in a bit.

437
00:25:15,146 --> 00:25:16,099
- Hurry and come down.
- Okay.

438
00:25:26,482 --> 00:25:27,042
Hey, Wayu!

439
00:25:29,555 --> 00:25:30,950
Hurry! Nice!

440
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:32,221
- Go, go!
- Come on!

441
00:25:36,813 --> 00:25:38,296
Hey, Wayu!

442
00:25:38,861 --> 00:25:41,002
- What are you doing?
- Ouch! What?

443
00:25:41,722 --> 00:25:42,432
Huh?

444
00:25:42,432 --> 00:25:44,830
- Awesome!
- My bad.

445
00:25:46,754 --> 00:25:49,262
Tai, don't forget to pay for the pitch.

446
00:25:49,721 --> 00:25:52,776
Yeah, I will get you guys back next time.

447
00:25:53,359 --> 00:25:55,390
4:0 and you're still talking?

448
00:25:55,390 --> 00:25:56,697
Darn it! Get away!

449
00:25:56,714 --> 00:25:57,968
Calm down.

450
00:25:58,091 --> 00:25:59,645
Go pack your stuff and meet at the club.

451
00:25:59,751 --> 00:26:00,881
- Okay, bro.
- Go!

452
00:26:00,970 --> 00:26:02,365
Get lost!

453
00:26:02,665 --> 00:26:04,307
You go!

454
00:26:05,561 --> 00:26:07,115
This is all on you, Wayu!

455
00:26:07,556 --> 00:26:09,408
I said I was sorry!

456
00:26:09,522 --> 00:26:10,602
Damn it!

457
00:26:20,747 --> 00:26:21,930
What's your problem?

458
00:26:21,930 --> 00:26:23,679
Do you have a death wish or something?

459
00:26:23,785 --> 00:26:26,257
Look at you, acting all sensible now.

460
00:26:27,122 --> 00:26:30,230
You already had to smoke the client's cigarettes,
and now you're smoking your own too?

461
00:26:30,318 --> 00:26:32,137
Mind your own business.

462
00:26:32,296 --> 00:26:33,709
Let me mind your business.

463
00:26:33,991 --> 00:26:36,128
So, you had dinner with the officer.

464
00:26:36,234 --> 00:26:37,647
Why'd you come back looking like this?

465
00:26:38,882 --> 00:26:39,362
Hey!

466
00:26:40,419 --> 00:26:42,503
Is there some juicy drama?
You haven't updated me at all.

467
00:26:43,615 --> 00:26:47,129
Wayu's been getting all "lovey-dovey"
with the Officer.

468
00:26:47,147 --> 00:26:49,902
Whoa, playing with
"government property" now?

469
00:26:49,902 --> 00:26:50,926
Is he a client?

470
00:26:50,926 --> 00:26:51,840
Hey! Hey!

471
00:26:52,180 --> 00:26:54,263
I'll tell you every single detail.

472
00:26:54,263 --> 00:26:55,500
But first,

473
00:26:55,605 --> 00:26:57,036
I need to update my patches.

474
00:26:57,442 --> 00:26:58,784
So, how is it?

475
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:02,899
Everything was great...

476
00:27:04,912 --> 00:27:06,130
Right up until his girlfriend showed up.

477
00:27:07,278 --> 00:27:08,814
Don't just give up!

478
00:27:08,814 --> 00:27:10,880
You're talking to the right person.

479
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:13,741
Stealing someone else's is my specialty!

480
00:27:15,312 --> 00:27:18,578
Let me see her profile.

481
00:27:22,853 --> 00:27:26,985
Rose Peerapa Siriharnphaiboon.

482
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:29,263
Owner of a fine-dining restaurant.

483
00:27:29,704 --> 00:27:34,861
Daughter of a tycoon.
Master's degree from England.

484
00:27:36,838 --> 00:27:38,057
Yeah, maybe find someone else.

485
00:27:38,622 --> 00:27:40,282
You can't compete with that.

486
00:27:41,962 --> 00:27:46,602
Ouch!

487
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:50,895
I'm confused.

488
00:27:53,844 --> 00:27:56,422
I feel like he actually feels
something for me.

489
00:27:58,576 --> 00:28:01,084
Look, having
a high-class sponsor is great.

490
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:04,351
But if you want to date for real,

491
00:28:04,509 --> 00:28:05,763
I think that will be tough.

492
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:08,306
You'd have to change your whole life, man.

493
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:11,220
I actually agree.

494
00:28:11,308 --> 00:28:14,274
Why don't you go to a shrine
and pray for someone else instead?

495
00:28:14,585 --> 00:28:16,881
I know plenty of good spots.
I'll take you there.

496
00:28:19,802 --> 00:28:21,002
Hey! Hey!

497
00:28:21,479 --> 00:28:22,857
Go be moody at the club.

498
00:28:23,263 --> 00:28:25,382
If you're late and get your pay docked,

499
00:28:25,382 --> 00:28:26,795
you'll be even more miserable.

500
00:28:26,816 --> 00:28:27,904
- Duh.
- Got it?

501
00:28:28,331 --> 00:28:31,069
The one who should be
having a hard time is you, Tai.

502
00:28:31,069 --> 00:28:33,311
You're the one who just broke a record.

503
00:28:33,311 --> 00:28:34,741
You were an hour late.

504
00:28:35,418 --> 00:28:37,024
- Won't you ever learn?
- Shut up!

505
00:28:37,408 --> 00:28:40,268
I lost 6,000 baht. I almost cried.

506
00:28:40,551 --> 00:28:42,546
Luckily, only cut the fine in half for me.

507
00:28:43,076 --> 00:28:44,806
And you lecturing me?

508
00:28:44,806 --> 00:28:45,974
- Hurry up! What are you waiting for?
- Hurry up!

509
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:46,837
What are you waiting for?

510
00:28:48,321 --> 00:28:49,574
That's a shame.

511
00:28:52,771 --> 00:28:54,554
One, two, three.

512
00:28:56,037 --> 00:28:57,627
One, two, three.

513
00:29:01,070 --> 00:29:01,900
One, two.

514
00:29:07,233 --> 00:29:08,010
You're beautiful.

515
00:29:09,988 --> 00:29:11,030
I love you.

516
00:29:12,124 --> 00:29:13,325
Thank you.

517
00:29:13,378 --> 00:29:14,791
I love you so much.

518
00:29:14,791 --> 00:29:16,168
Promise you'll only love me, okay?

519
00:29:18,436 --> 00:29:19,306
Richy.

520
00:29:20,318 --> 00:29:21,925
- Take a photo for me.
- Sure thing.

521
00:29:22,366 --> 00:29:23,532
A full-body shot.

522
00:29:23,532 --> 00:29:24,832
Full-car. The car on the right.

523
00:29:25,562 --> 00:29:27,392
Shoot!

524
00:29:27,505 --> 00:29:29,995
Having a sponsor is great and all,

525
00:29:30,436 --> 00:29:31,973
but I don't think it's worth dealing
with someone like him.

526
00:29:31,973 --> 00:29:35,081
Being a "Top-Tier" host. Life's a breeze.

527
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:37,517
Top-tier? More like top-tier trash.

528
00:29:37,517 --> 00:29:38,789
One, two, three.

529
00:29:39,795 --> 00:29:40,882
Want to check the photo?

530
00:29:40,882 --> 00:29:42,082
- Hey, let me see. Is it good?
- What're you doing?

531
00:29:42,179 --> 00:29:43,539
Thank you.

532
00:29:45,022 --> 00:29:46,753
With a brand new plate too.

533
00:29:47,442 --> 00:29:48,722
You're actually serving today.

534
00:29:48,722 --> 00:29:50,082
Yeah.

535
00:29:51,485 --> 00:29:53,304
Sky, why did you do this to me?

536
00:29:53,304 --> 00:29:54,152
What are you doing?

537
00:29:54,152 --> 00:29:58,902
- You got one car yesterday, and another one today.
- Explain this! Why? The car was just bought yesterday.

538
00:29:58,937 --> 00:30:00,898
- You're so kind.
- Do you know how much this car costs?

539
00:30:01,321 --> 00:30:02,081
Tai!

540
00:30:03,035 --> 00:30:03,775
Enough.

541
00:30:03,775 --> 00:30:05,347
- What do you want to do?
- You're fooling me, aren't you?

542
00:30:05,402 --> 00:30:06,972
- Get inside.
- You're fooling me, right?

543
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:08,244
- It's 100 baht fine per minute late!
- You played me.

544
00:30:08,244 --> 00:30:10,839
- Do you have a problem?
- Enough.

545
00:30:10,839 --> 00:30:11,669
- Let's go.
- Right?

546
00:30:11,936 --> 00:30:13,489
- I'll go first.
- Explain this to me.

547
00:30:13,541 --> 00:30:14,300
You think I'm stupid?

548
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:16,300
Richy, my phone.

549
00:30:16,762 --> 00:30:17,408
That's enough.

550
00:30:18,097 --> 00:30:20,481
Good job. Next up is Kenji.

551
00:30:20,481 --> 00:30:22,159
Come to the mark spot and pose.

552
00:30:22,159 --> 00:30:25,088
- If only you could play football better today.
- Ugh, come on.

553
00:30:25,088 --> 00:30:26,920
I said I was sorry!

554
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,527
Lean back. Show them what you've got.

555
00:30:28,527 --> 00:30:30,970
- Alright. Go practice.
- Got it.

556
00:30:31,402 --> 00:30:31,802
Hey!

557
00:30:32,506 --> 00:30:34,007
I'm telling you, we have to prove

558
00:30:34,007 --> 00:30:37,257
if that cop is just dating
that girl for show.

559
00:30:39,005 --> 00:30:40,223
I don't care anymore.

560
00:30:40,965 --> 00:30:42,254
I'm over it. I'm moving on.

561
00:30:43,702 --> 00:30:45,503
Moving on? Okay.

562
00:30:45,609 --> 00:30:46,739
- Wayu!
- Yes.

563
00:30:46,739 --> 00:30:48,523
You might be over it, but I'm not!

564
00:30:53,979 --> 00:30:56,098
(MONDAY DISCOUNT 30% OFF)
Come to the mark spot.

565
00:30:57,211 --> 00:30:58,800
(Monday discount.)

566
00:30:59,206 --> 00:31:01,996
Look left, look right.

567
00:31:02,403 --> 00:31:03,974
Yeah, go.

568
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:07,936
You guys better start focusing.

569
00:31:07,936 --> 00:31:10,656
- You guys better start focusing.
- Tai!

570
00:31:11,162 --> 00:31:12,762
(MONDAY DISCOUNT)

571
00:31:13,669 --> 00:31:14,781
Tai!

572
00:31:14,958 --> 00:31:17,059
What are you doing?
Why didn't you consult me first?

573
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:20,944
Don't worry, friend.
One day you'll thank me.

574
00:31:20,962 --> 00:31:22,321
Thank you for what?

575
00:31:22,321 --> 00:31:23,628
Tell me what you're doing first!

576
00:31:24,082 --> 00:31:25,442
Whoa, damn it!

577
00:31:25,442 --> 00:31:27,922
Ouch!

578
00:31:28,096 --> 00:31:30,586
You two! Why didn't you finish
playing around yesterday?

579
00:31:30,656 --> 00:31:31,928
What a shot! Scary accurate.

580
00:31:32,104 --> 00:31:32,899
Come here!

581
00:31:33,376 --> 00:31:34,683
Bring me my stick too!

582
00:31:35,642 --> 00:31:36,310
Hmm.

583
00:31:38,664 --> 00:31:40,734
(Krit: I'm usually pretty busy on Mondays.
Maybe some other time)

584
00:31:40,757 --> 00:31:42,046
Hey, come down here.

585
00:31:44,448 --> 00:31:47,044
Oh, is this all you've got
to show? See here?

586
00:31:48,085 --> 00:31:49,586
I'll keep it. This is your stick.

587
00:31:51,123 --> 00:31:52,500
- Wayu!
- Yes.

588
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:54,072
Where are you supposed to be?

589
00:31:54,072 --> 00:31:55,926
Over there with your friends!

590
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:57,921
Useless.

591
00:31:59,246 --> 00:32:02,018
Richy, where have you been?

592
00:32:02,230 --> 00:32:04,685
Did you know my Sugar Momma
already seized my car?

593
00:32:05,002 --> 00:32:06,592
Tai is so bad!

594
00:32:06,927 --> 00:32:07,969
Darn it!

595
00:32:09,364 --> 00:32:12,154
Don't let him get away with it, bro.
Get back at him!

596
00:32:18,705 --> 00:32:19,412
Wayu.

597
00:32:20,666 --> 00:32:21,690
Where's your friend Tai?

598
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:24,162
I haven't seen him.

599
00:32:27,747 --> 00:32:29,742
Friends have to look out
for each other, right?

600
00:32:31,314 --> 00:32:34,051
Fine. You guys just wait.

601
00:32:40,955 --> 00:32:42,915
I really haven't seen him, Sky.

602
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:48,319
Why are you acting so polite?

603
00:32:49,119 --> 00:32:50,364
Go.

604
00:33:00,503 --> 00:33:02,305
(Wayu browses Spotify,
looking for songs to listen to,)

605
00:33:02,305 --> 00:33:03,735
(and adds several songs to the playlist)

606
00:33:03,735 --> 00:33:05,148
(All of them are love songs)

607
00:33:05,148 --> 00:33:06,561
(Named the playlist as)

608
00:33:06,561 --> 00:33:08,273
("Is My Heart Fluttering Because of
Baking Soda or Because of You?")

609
00:33:09,033 --> 00:33:10,940
(Wayu shared the playlist he just created)

610
00:33:10,957 --> 00:33:16,064
(on his Instagram page)

611
00:33:16,064 --> 00:33:18,091
(Wayu shared the playlist to his story)

612
00:33:18,127 --> 00:33:19,751
(with the caption saying,)

613
00:33:19,751 --> 00:33:24,713
("Miss everyone,
please don't forget to come tonight")

614
00:33:24,713 --> 00:33:26,144
(Wayu repeatedly refreshed to see
who viewed his post)

615
00:33:26,144 --> 00:33:27,698
(Saw that only Tai viewed it)

616
00:33:30,788 --> 00:33:34,548
"Is My Heart Fluttering Because of
Baking Soda or Because of You?"

617
00:33:34,638 --> 00:33:35,980
Dude, what time exactly did you "move on"?

618
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:37,304
Shut up, Tai!

619
00:33:37,522 --> 00:33:39,104
Easy!

620
00:33:40,147 --> 00:33:42,602
What happened?

621
00:33:43,838 --> 00:33:45,692
It's about Wayu.

622
00:33:45,868 --> 00:33:48,517
He's about to "swallow"
some government property.

623
00:33:48,522 --> 00:33:51,522
Huh?

624
00:33:57,753 --> 00:33:58,812
A cop?

625
00:33:59,448 --> 00:34:00,437
Tai!

626
00:34:02,715 --> 00:34:03,845
Impossible.

627
00:34:04,410 --> 00:34:06,706
Give it a rest, Wayu.
Don't get yourself hurt.

628
00:34:07,748 --> 00:34:11,156
Cops are all just
playing around with bar hosts.

629
00:34:21,786 --> 00:34:23,464
Copy that.

630
00:34:25,706 --> 00:34:27,366
So unfaithful.

631
00:34:29,009 --> 00:34:31,799
It's good if the cops show up here.

632
00:34:31,799 --> 00:34:34,368
Then he won't be out there
stealing my customers.

633
00:34:34,368 --> 00:34:35,258
I totally agree.

634
00:34:38,592 --> 00:34:40,540
Hey! What are you all doing?

635
00:34:41,317 --> 00:34:42,659
What are you all doing?

636
00:34:43,806 --> 00:34:45,043
Why are you standing still?

637
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:48,098
- What a waste of time.
- Here, here.

638
00:34:48,098 --> 00:34:48,705
A little bit.

639
00:34:49,298 --> 00:34:50,835
- You two too!
- Yes!

640
00:34:50,835 --> 00:34:52,918
- Get ready, now!
- Yes.

641
00:34:52,918 --> 00:34:54,944
These kids.
They have no clue what's going on.

642
00:34:54,944 --> 00:34:56,980
When it's time to work, just go work!

643
00:34:56,980 --> 00:34:58,993
When did those guys get here?

644
00:34:58,993 --> 00:35:01,077
No idea. I just noticed them too.

645
00:35:04,122 --> 00:35:08,378
(IG: Wayu__you)

646
00:35:20,634 --> 00:35:26,107
♪There's no one else
who makes me fall in love♪

647
00:35:26,107 --> 00:35:28,970
♪As much as you do♪

648
00:35:29,666 --> 00:35:30,567
Just take it and look.

649
00:35:32,050 --> 00:35:34,399
Stalking his IG, huh?
Do you have any feelings for him?

650
00:35:37,524 --> 00:35:39,572
Oh, you've totally got feelings for him!

651
00:35:40,597 --> 00:35:41,586
No, I don't.

652
00:35:43,828 --> 00:35:45,700
Sorry I introduced myself like that.

653
00:35:45,718 --> 00:35:47,748
He must've misunderstood.

654
00:35:49,479 --> 00:35:50,768
Don't be ridiculous.

655
00:35:51,951 --> 00:35:53,717
I'm being serious here.

656
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:56,913
Open your heart for once!
Get yourself a life.

657
00:35:57,937 --> 00:36:01,222
Officer, you have a 'gun,'
you'd better use it

658
00:36:01,222 --> 00:36:03,288
before it gets rusty and misfires.

659
00:36:05,354 --> 00:36:08,868
I wish your mom could see this
and have a heart attack.

660
00:36:09,274 --> 00:36:11,606
Go ahead. I'll reveal that
we're only dating for show.

661
00:36:11,606 --> 00:36:12,771
Let's go down together.

662
00:36:12,771 --> 00:36:14,272
So my mom will be shocked all at once.

663
00:36:17,203 --> 00:36:18,704
I wanted to say since that day.

664
00:36:19,322 --> 00:36:21,000
One day we'll have to tell the truth.

665
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:22,977
We can't keep this fake dating
act up forever.

666
00:36:23,048 --> 00:36:24,337
It's impossible.

667
00:36:27,551 --> 00:36:28,452
I know.

668
00:36:34,138 --> 00:36:37,016
Anyway, we'll get through this together.

669
00:36:37,299 --> 00:36:38,093
Right?

670
00:36:39,612 --> 00:36:40,371
Right.

671
00:36:45,510 --> 00:36:46,446
I didn't see it.

672
00:37:01,754 --> 00:37:07,616
(Krit.Siri started following you just now.
Message)

673
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:12,563
Wayu, are you okay?

674
00:37:12,792 --> 00:37:14,046
Are you hurt?

675
00:37:15,759 --> 00:37:17,189
Don't bother helping him.

676
00:37:17,189 --> 00:37:19,432
Leave those "crazy-in-love" fools

677
00:37:19,591 --> 00:37:21,092
to rot right there on the floor.

678
00:37:23,458 --> 00:37:26,955
Bro. If you'd slid like that
on the football pitch, we would've won!

679
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:28,826
Exactly! You're spot on.

680
00:37:29,427 --> 00:37:30,292
Come on.

681
00:37:30,998 --> 00:37:32,641
Let's leave him alone.

682
00:37:33,100 --> 00:37:36,367
Let the love-sick fool

683
00:37:36,367 --> 00:37:37,620
stay in the bathroom

684
00:37:37,620 --> 00:37:38,482
all by himself!

685
00:37:38,482 --> 00:37:39,194
Let's go, bro.

686
00:38:03,137 --> 00:38:04,903
Same as usual, Wayu.

687
00:38:07,622 --> 00:38:08,753
Whoa, ma'am!

688
00:38:09,017 --> 00:38:11,137
You're getting worse every day.

689
00:38:11,454 --> 00:38:15,145
Ever since Wayu showed up,
I never get a big portion anymore!

690
00:38:15,728 --> 00:38:17,917
Portions are based on looks.

691
00:38:18,165 --> 00:38:20,478
Oh, Mr. Privilege!

692
00:38:20,566 --> 00:38:23,127
So this is that "Privilege"
everyone's talking about, huh?

693
00:38:23,144 --> 00:38:25,811
What privilege? Can't you see
I get the same amount as you?

694
00:38:25,864 --> 00:38:27,771
Stop! Shut up!

695
00:38:29,872 --> 00:38:32,574
There are some for your mom
and Singto. It's on me.

696
00:38:32,574 --> 00:38:33,528
Don't forget to pick them up.

697
00:38:33,545 --> 00:38:34,941
No, It's fine.

698
00:38:34,941 --> 00:38:35,671
I can't do that.

699
00:38:35,671 --> 00:38:37,007
Everyone works just as hard.

700
00:38:37,007 --> 00:38:38,755
- I insist on paying, okay?
- Hmm.

701
00:38:38,755 --> 00:38:40,132
Please, Ms. Beauty.

702
00:38:40,132 --> 00:38:41,668
- Please.
- Fine, you can pay.

703
00:38:41,668 --> 00:38:43,402
But I'm giving you an extra-large portion.
Even bigger than this.

704
00:38:43,402 --> 00:38:44,202
- More than this.
- Okay.

705
00:38:44,410 --> 00:38:45,689
Oh, please!

706
00:38:46,118 --> 00:38:48,361
Isn't that enough already?

707
00:38:48,361 --> 00:38:49,579
Zip it.

708
00:38:56,307 --> 00:38:57,120
Tai.

709
00:38:57,402 --> 00:38:59,962
Huh?

710
00:39:00,104 --> 00:39:01,570
He accepted my request.

711
00:39:03,602 --> 00:39:04,922
Hmm.

712
00:39:04,942 --> 00:39:07,750
I think you should take
Foei's advice seriously.

713
00:39:07,962 --> 00:39:09,816
Foei might be right.

714
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,688
He might be approaching you

715
00:39:11,829 --> 00:39:13,807
because he wants something from you.

716
00:39:19,402 --> 00:39:20,682
Oh.

717
00:39:20,729 --> 00:39:22,813
But no matter what his angle is,

718
00:39:23,325 --> 00:39:25,267
make sure you get some "action"
out of it. You feel me?

719
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,475
You're so obsessed.

720
00:39:28,762 --> 00:39:29,162
Hey!

721
00:39:29,647 --> 00:39:31,784
I'd better text my clients.

722
00:39:35,602 --> 00:39:37,312
So little.

723
00:39:38,494 --> 00:39:39,536
(Chainphop Udomdirek, 32)

724
00:39:39,536 --> 00:39:40,683
(Export business owner)

725
00:39:40,683 --> 00:39:41,743
(C Group Logistics)

726
00:39:41,743 --> 00:39:43,968
Several individuals were last seen
with Chainphop before they vanished.

727
00:39:44,427 --> 00:39:45,751
There are reports

728
00:39:46,052 --> 00:39:48,188
(Reported missing by relatives)
of frequent disappearances around Soi 2.

729
00:39:50,007 --> 00:39:51,897
I think we need to
start the fieldwork immediately.

730
00:39:52,886 --> 00:39:53,786
When do we start?

731
00:39:54,952 --> 00:39:55,976
I want to go today.

732
00:39:56,541 --> 00:39:59,154
I'm not available today, Captain.

733
00:39:59,384 --> 00:40:01,379
I've already made plans
with my wife and kids.

734
00:40:04,487 --> 00:40:05,264
Don't worry about it.

735
00:40:05,776 --> 00:40:06,783
I only just decided on it myself.

736
00:40:07,825 --> 00:40:09,608
Just keep me posted on any progress.

737
00:40:10,332 --> 00:40:11,409
Thank you, Captain.

738
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:12,504
See you tomorrow.

739
00:40:17,978 --> 00:40:19,674
(Reported missing by relatives)

740
00:40:19,674 --> 00:40:21,404
(5th January 2025, 8:24 PM)

741
00:40:21,404 --> 00:40:22,994
(Entered a hotel in the Silom area
with Chainphop)

742
00:40:44,378 --> 00:40:46,109
As modern-day police officers,

743
00:40:46,109 --> 00:40:51,265
we focus on using technology
for transparency in all cases.

744
00:41:19,484 --> 00:41:21,533
♪Standing confused
in the crowd of love-struck people♪

745
00:41:21,562 --> 00:41:24,321
♪Walking closely together past me♪

746
00:41:24,327 --> 00:41:27,916
♪Hurts that I'm the only one still alone♪

747
00:41:27,959 --> 00:41:29,854
♪Why are they walking holding hands?♪

748
00:41:29,894 --> 00:41:36,149
♪It's annoying,
the more I see it the more it hurts♪

749
00:41:36,162 --> 00:41:40,334
♪No one understands♪

750
00:41:40,342 --> 00:41:43,878
♪I'm a victim of loneliness♪

751
00:41:43,891 --> 00:41:50,005
♪I want to meet someone
who shares my feelings♪

752
00:41:50,032 --> 00:41:53,939
♪Still praying to be loved♪

753
00:41:53,958 --> 00:41:58,606
♪Waiting for someone to touch my heart♪

754
00:41:58,679 --> 00:42:02,285
♪I want someone to hold hands with♪

755
00:42:02,307 --> 00:42:06,426
♪Before I die of loneliness♪

756
00:42:06,483 --> 00:42:09,348
♪Help me. That's all I need♪

757
00:42:09,379 --> 00:42:13,356
♪Just someone. Help me. That's all I need♪

758
00:42:13,370 --> 00:42:16,570
♪Just someone♪

759
00:42:30,810 --> 00:42:31,460
Hey!

760
00:42:31,460 --> 00:42:33,473
Look at him, sitting comfortably.

761
00:42:33,773 --> 00:42:36,069
That customer spent a fortune to book him.
He's acting so smug.

762
00:42:36,510 --> 00:42:37,853
Well, don't just stand there and take it!

763
00:42:38,064 --> 00:42:39,744
Go get those tips and drinks for yourself.

764
00:42:39,842 --> 00:42:40,642
Yeah.

765
00:42:40,784 --> 00:42:42,709
Fine, let's see who can pull in more.

766
00:42:42,832 --> 00:42:45,393
You're on.
I've got plenty of debts to pay too.

767
00:42:45,393 --> 00:42:46,717
Go for it, man!

768
00:42:46,717 --> 00:42:47,653
Let's do it, man!

769
00:43:48,893 --> 00:43:49,882
Give it your all, man!

770
00:44:24,316 --> 00:44:25,570
Where did you go?

771
00:44:39,162 --> 00:44:42,162
Thank you.

772
00:44:47,414 --> 00:44:48,262
Wow, you're amazing.

773
00:44:48,473 --> 00:44:50,222
I'm definitely taking notes on your moves.

774
00:44:58,627 --> 00:45:01,188
Play a game with me.

775
00:45:01,205 --> 00:45:01,806
- Please.
- Sure.

776
00:45:01,806 --> 00:45:03,660
Let's play Rock-Paper-Scissors.

777
00:45:04,084 --> 00:45:05,744
What happens to the loser?

778
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:07,368
If you lose, you drink.

779
00:45:07,474 --> 00:45:09,116
- Alright, let's do it.
- Okay, let's go.

780
00:45:09,187 --> 00:45:12,754
Rock, Paper, Scissors...

781
00:45:13,814 --> 00:45:15,632
- Drink.
- I lost.

782
00:45:15,632 --> 00:45:17,602
How do I get you drunk, huh?

783
00:45:17,602 --> 00:45:19,392
Oh.

784
00:45:20,224 --> 00:45:21,707
Better luck next round, Radee.

785
00:45:21,707 --> 00:45:22,943
Drink up.

786
00:45:23,879 --> 00:45:25,115
Wayu, drink this for me, please?

787
00:45:25,115 --> 00:45:27,517
It'll give me the strength
to keep playing with you.

788
00:45:27,517 --> 00:45:28,576
Please?

789
00:45:28,576 --> 00:45:30,112
Okay.

790
00:45:30,112 --> 00:45:30,836
Hello.

791
00:45:30,836 --> 00:45:32,655
Tall and handsome.

792
00:45:32,655 --> 00:45:34,174
I've already given you a discount.

793
00:45:34,174 --> 00:45:35,551
Really.

794
00:45:35,551 --> 00:45:37,105
Take care of her.

795
00:45:37,282 --> 00:45:40,443
You take such good care of me, Tai.

796
00:45:40,584 --> 00:45:42,491
Do you have many regulars?

797
00:45:42,509 --> 00:45:45,158
None at all.

798
00:45:45,158 --> 00:45:48,071
Since I started working,
you're the very first one.

799
00:45:48,266 --> 00:45:49,767
Really?

800
00:45:50,242 --> 00:45:51,322
Hey!

801
00:45:51,409 --> 00:45:53,899
Then why did you invite me today
only to end up busy with another client?

802
00:45:53,962 --> 00:45:55,962
Uh.

803
00:45:56,071 --> 00:45:58,808
You're acting confused now
that you're with her?

804
00:45:58,808 --> 00:46:01,475
Weren't you the one
who got Sky to invite me?

805
00:46:01,475 --> 00:46:02,375
It's alright.

806
00:46:03,540 --> 00:46:04,388
Sky, you...

807
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:07,107
Tai, I thought you said
you didn't have any regulars!

808
00:46:07,566 --> 00:46:09,156
Calm down, Bua.

809
00:46:09,527 --> 00:46:11,204
Calm down, Yok.

810
00:46:12,899 --> 00:46:16,254
I've already booked Tai
for the whole night.

811
00:46:16,730 --> 00:46:18,202
Why don't you just go home, Old Madam?

812
00:46:18,202 --> 00:46:21,202
Hey!

813
00:46:21,428 --> 00:46:23,034
Let's go talk outside, Yok.

814
00:46:23,547 --> 00:46:25,031
Wait for me here, okay?
I'll be right back.

815
00:46:25,031 --> 00:46:26,620
- Wait for me.
- No!

816
00:46:27,662 --> 00:46:29,905
If you leave, cancel the drinks.

817
00:46:32,359 --> 00:46:33,472
Don't worry.

818
00:46:33,472 --> 00:46:34,602
I'll handle this.

819
00:46:34,602 --> 00:46:37,198
Have your drink. I'll take care of it.

820
00:46:39,864 --> 00:46:42,531
Please calm down, Bua.

821
00:46:42,531 --> 00:46:43,996
I'll get someone new for you.

822
00:46:43,996 --> 00:46:46,751
- Yok.
- I guarantee you'll love this one.

823
00:46:46,751 --> 00:46:47,669
Just a moment, please.

824
00:46:47,969 --> 00:46:50,247
No! I'm leaving.

825
00:46:50,353 --> 00:46:52,437
Radee, let's go!

826
00:46:53,461 --> 00:46:54,752
- I'm not going.
- Bua.

827
00:46:54,752 --> 00:46:55,262
Hurry.

828
00:46:55,262 --> 00:46:59,023
- Radee.
- Wayu, I'll be back soon, okay?

829
00:46:59,165 --> 00:47:00,560
Stop being so clingy!

830
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:02,520
- I paid for drinks and got nothing. Terrible!
- Wayu!

831
00:47:04,074 --> 00:47:06,656
- Let's go.
- Bua, I'll escort you out.

832
00:47:07,682 --> 00:47:10,682
Now, don't be afraid.

833
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:17,777
Darn it! I got dragged into this mess too.

834
00:47:20,285 --> 00:47:20,956
Cigarette.

835
00:47:22,227 --> 00:47:24,805
(Silom Moonlight)
I just want one cigarette, not the pack.

836
00:47:25,635 --> 00:47:27,083
Cigarette. Money.

837
00:47:28,178 --> 00:47:30,279
What's with this guy?
I can't understand a word he's saying.

838
00:47:32,239 --> 00:47:34,217
Tobacco. Money.

839
00:47:34,517 --> 00:47:36,058
One. One cigarette.

840
00:47:36,058 --> 00:47:38,208
Jang, is everything okay?

841
00:47:38,950 --> 00:47:41,157
Wayu! Help me out here.

842
00:47:41,157 --> 00:47:43,312
My phone's dead, and I can't open Google.

843
00:47:43,802 --> 00:47:44,864
- Hi
- Hi.

844
00:47:44,864 --> 00:47:45,784
May I help you?

845
00:47:45,784 --> 00:47:48,503
I just want one cigarette, not the pack.

846
00:47:49,351 --> 00:47:51,452
But buying a pack is cheaper.

847
00:47:51,452 --> 00:47:53,659
Definitely cheaper
than convenience stores.

848
00:47:53,659 --> 00:47:58,056
And we've got menthols too.
Twice as cheap as other shops around here.

849
00:47:58,780 --> 00:48:00,847
Alright. Alright. I'll take it.

850
00:48:00,900 --> 00:48:02,206
Okay, thank you.

851
00:48:03,901 --> 00:48:04,714
40 baht.

852
00:48:08,970 --> 00:48:09,941
Thank you.

853
00:48:09,941 --> 00:48:12,571
- Thanks a lot.
- Thank you.

854
00:48:12,571 --> 00:48:13,296
Thank you.

855
00:48:13,296 --> 00:48:15,750
Thank you. Thanks a lot.

856
00:48:16,633 --> 00:48:17,693
Good job, Jang.

857
00:48:17,975 --> 00:48:21,931
Wayu, you speak English
so fast, like a pro.

858
00:48:22,408 --> 00:48:25,744
- That's why you need to study hard, Jang.
- Right.

859
00:48:25,802 --> 00:48:28,871
- Woo!
- So when you grow up, you can talk to foreigners too.

860
00:48:30,566 --> 00:48:31,749
To be honest,

861
00:48:31,872 --> 00:48:32,314
Hmm.

862
00:48:32,314 --> 00:48:34,363
I want to be like you and Tai.

863
00:48:34,716 --> 00:48:37,170
It probably pays way better
than being a fresh grad.

864
00:48:37,382 --> 00:48:40,384
You get nice things,
and people even buy cars for you.

865
00:48:42,627 --> 00:48:43,704
Listen to me, Jang.

866
00:48:44,022 --> 00:48:45,841
I don't think you should take this path.

867
00:48:46,388 --> 00:48:48,260
It's not that it's "bad,"

868
00:48:48,278 --> 00:48:50,255
but there's a lot
you have to sacrifice in exchange.

869
00:48:51,138 --> 00:48:52,639
You're still young.

870
00:48:52,675 --> 00:48:53,999
Keep it for later.

871
00:48:53,999 --> 00:48:56,877
Go explore the world first
and then decide.

872
00:48:57,602 --> 00:48:58,962
Whoa!

873
00:48:58,996 --> 00:49:01,186
You give better advice than my dad.

874
00:49:01,186 --> 00:49:05,035
He told me as soon as I turn 19,
I should go apply for a host job.

875
00:49:05,813 --> 00:49:08,144
Take it with a grain of salt, Jang.

876
00:49:08,691 --> 00:49:11,834
As a "Gen Alpha" kid,
you need to do your research.

877
00:49:12,982 --> 00:49:15,029
- Got it?
- Got it.

878
00:49:15,207 --> 00:49:16,302
And one more thing,

879
00:49:16,478 --> 00:49:18,403
don't go selling
in those dark alleys, okay?

880
00:49:18,721 --> 00:49:20,875
I know.

881
00:49:21,370 --> 00:49:22,359
Yes, I know.

882
00:49:22,535 --> 00:49:23,328
Very good.

883
00:49:23,522 --> 00:49:24,802
Yes.

884
00:49:24,884 --> 00:49:25,838
Now turn off the lights.

885
00:49:26,102 --> 00:49:27,056
No way. I like it this way.

886
00:49:29,087 --> 00:49:30,817
- Okay, I'm heading out then.
- Okay.

887
00:49:31,578 --> 00:49:35,082
Whoa, tung, tung, tung, sahura.

888
00:49:35,322 --> 00:49:36,712
Talale, talala.

889
00:49:36,954 --> 00:49:41,607
Champagnezinie, banananie.
Cappuccino azazino.

890
00:49:49,306 --> 00:49:51,496
Look at him.

891
00:49:51,672 --> 00:49:54,339
Heading into a dark alley.

892
00:50:21,442 --> 00:50:24,442
Hey!

893
00:50:30,486 --> 00:50:31,881
Planning to ambush an officer?

894
00:50:33,894 --> 00:50:35,342
I'm not here to ambush you.

895
00:50:36,084 --> 00:50:37,673
I'm here to catch you, Officer.

896
00:50:37,673 --> 00:50:39,015
I wonder why you are here?

897
00:50:46,025 --> 00:50:46,979
Why do you ask?

898
00:50:48,305 --> 00:50:50,305
Because this is a dark alley.

899
00:50:50,306 --> 00:50:51,512
Known as a "spicy" alley.

900
00:50:51,890 --> 00:50:54,190
People come here to get intimate.

901
00:50:54,784 --> 00:50:55,667
But you,

902
00:50:56,144 --> 00:50:59,322
does your girlfriend know
you're hanging around here?

903
00:51:02,589 --> 00:51:03,755
I'm working on a case.

904
00:51:04,850 --> 00:51:06,139
Even better.

905
00:51:06,139 --> 00:51:08,116
I'm a local. I can help you.

906
00:51:09,494 --> 00:51:11,207
It's classified information.

907
00:51:12,690 --> 00:51:15,763
You're investigating the disappearances
around Soi 2, aren't you?

908
00:51:17,422 --> 00:51:20,071
People around here already know.

909
00:51:21,113 --> 00:51:23,020
I even know

910
00:51:23,903 --> 00:51:26,269
exactly which alleys

911
00:51:26,517 --> 00:51:28,000
are considered dangerous.

912
00:51:29,377 --> 00:51:31,020
Come on. Let me help.

913
00:51:31,284 --> 00:51:33,474
I'm a local. I can be your guide.

914
00:51:34,922 --> 00:51:36,335
That's not necessary.

915
00:51:38,277 --> 00:51:39,213
You sure?

916
00:51:50,956 --> 00:51:53,075
I've even got
a "free trial" promo for you.

917
00:52:23,748 --> 00:52:25,055
Hey, sweetie,

918
00:52:25,391 --> 00:52:26,521
